sections.content:
If you try to send on a channel and nothing is receiving, your program will deadlock. Same if you try to receive and nothing is sending.

```go
// THIS WILL DEADLOCK:
func main() {
    ch := make(chan int)
    ch <- 42  // Send, but no goroutine is receiving!
    // main is the only goroutine, and it's blocked here
}
```

Go detects this and panics: `fatal error: all goroutines are asleep - deadlock!`

